The evidence with the title 'Race and the War On Drugs - Wikipedia ' says Professor Cathy Schnieder of International Service at American University notes that in 1989 , African Americans, representing 12-15 percent of all drug use in the United States , made up 41 percent of all arrests. That is a noted increase from 38 percent in 1988 . Whites were 47 percent of those in state-funded treatment  ... 
